  "text": "We then moved on to study the mechanisms of Rac1 in stimulating axonal regeneration after stroke. MEK1/2 and ERK1/2 are well-known pro-regenerative molecules, as they stimulate the expression of pro-regenerative genes. Importantly, Rac1 is known to activate MEK (via PAK1), which then phosphorylates ERK. Additionally, Rac1 also targets LIMK1, another potent enhancer of axonal plasticity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . As expected, we found that delayed inhibition of Rac1 reduced the levels of p-LIMK 1 (day 14, vehicle 1.47 ± 0.09 vs. NSC 0.75 ± 0.12, n = 4, ",
